content:
This component renders the main Integrations page within the DocMed dashboard. It displays connected repository pairs, allowing users to manage their documentation integration workflows.

## Purpose

The `IntegrationsPage` serves as the central hub for users to view, add, and manage connections between their source code repositories and documentation repositories. It fetches a list of configured repository pairs and displays them using `RepoPairCard` components. It also handles potential configuration errors during the fetching process and provides guidance when no integrations are set up.

## Key Features

*   **Authentication**: Leverages Clerk's `auth` to get the current `userId`.
*   **Repository Pair Management**: Fetches and displays a list of connected repository pairs using the `listRepoPairs` utility.
*   **Error Handling**: Catches and displays errors related to fetching repository configurations, specifically highlighting potential Firebase issues.
*   **Empty State**: Provides a user-friendly message and icon when no repository pairs are configured, guiding the user to add one.
*   **Conditional Rendering**: Dynamically renders content based on whether there are configuration errors or if the list of pairs is empty.

## Components Used

*   `@clerk/nextjs/server`: For user authentication.
*   `@/lib/repo-pairs`: Contains the `listRepoPairs` function to fetch repository configurations.
*   `./_components/RepoPairCard`: A component to display individual repository pair details.
*   `./_components/AddPairButton`: A button component to initiate the process of adding a new repository pair.
*   `lucide-react`: For the `GitBranch` icon used in the empty state.

## Usage Example

This component is intended to be used as a page within the Next.js application router. It does not require any specific props for rendering.

```typescript
// app/dashboard/integrations/page.tsx
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";
import { listRepoPairs } from "@/lib/repo-pairs";
import { RepoPairCard } from "./_components/RepoPairCard";
import { AddPairButton } from "./_components/AddPairButton";
import { GitBranch } from "lucide-react";

export default async function IntegrationsPage() {
  const { userId } = await auth();

  let pairs: Awaited<ReturnType<typeof listRepoPairs>> = [];
  let configError: string | null = null;

  try {
    pairs = await listRepoPairs(userId!); // Assumes userId is always present after auth
  } catch (err) {
    configError = err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err);
  }

  return (
    <div className="flex flex-col h-full p-8">
      {/* ... rest of the component's JSX ... */}
      <div className="flex items-start justify-between mb-8 gap-4">
        <div>
          <h1 className="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground tracking-tight">
            Integrations
          </h1>
          <p className="text-muted-foreground text-sm mt-1">
            Connect repository pairs — DocMed reads from the target and writes
            healed docs to the doc repo.
          </p>
        </div>
        <AddPairButton />
      </div>

      {configError && (
        <div className="mb-6 rounded-lg border border-yellow-500/20 bg-yellow-500/5 px-4 py-3 text-sm text-yellow-400">
          <p className="font-medium">Firebase error</p>
          <p className="mt-1 font-mono text-xs opacity-80">{configError}</p>
        </div>
      )}

      {!configError && pairs.length === 0 && (
        <div className="flex flex-col items-center justify-center flex-1 gap-3 text-center">
          <div className="size-12 rounded-xl bg-muted flex items-center justify-center">
            <GitBranch className="size-5 text-muted-foreground" />
          </div>
          <p className="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
            No repository pairs yet. Add one to get started.
          </p>
        </div>
      )}

      {pairs.length > 0 && (
        <div className="flex flex-col gap-4 max-w-2xl">
          {pairs.map((pair) => (
            <RepoPairCard key={pair.id} pair={pair} />
          ))}
        </div>
      )}
    </div>
  );
}
```
